title: Pre-Assessment
description: Answer the below questions to the best of your knowledge.

elements.name: repeat_question_titile
elements.html: What will be said sequentially on the stage, when this code is run?

elements.name: question1
elements.html: To ensure "here" is said 10 times, which number should be filled in the repeat block to replace the ??? block?

elements.name: question7
elements.html: What will be said sequentially on the stage, when this code is run? (sequential outputs are separated by ;)

elements.name: question11
elements.html: What will be said when this code is run?

elements.name: question10
elements.html:
Select programs from below that allows the sprite to say “hello” for 2 seconds, each time when the space key is pressed.
There may be more than one correct answer.

elements.name: question9
elements.html:
The below program include two sprites. A bear sprite and an apple sprite.
For the bear sprite, select code from below that will allow the bear to say “Yummy!” for 2 seconds, each time when it touches the apple.

Assuming there’s code (unshown) that allows the bear to hit the apple multiple times.

elements.name: concurrency_title
elements.html: Below are the code for a sprite in the program. What will happen to the sprite when the green flag is clicked?

choices.text: The sprite will turn and change size non-stop.
The sprite will first turn 15 degrees and change size by 10, then stop.
The sprite will only turn non-stop and will not change size.
The sprite will only change size non-stop and will not turn.

elements.name: question22
elements.html: Answer questions based on the following code.

elements.name: concurrency_1
elements.title: The above code change the value of x variable at every 2 seconds. At every 2  seconds, what will be the value of x?

choices.text: It will be a random value between 1 to 10

elements.name: concurrency_2
elements.title: When running the above code for a long time (e.g., 1 million seconds), what will be printed on the stage over time? (What will the sprite say over time)?

choices.text: The sprite will say 5 for 1 second, at every 2 seconds.
The sprite will say “x” for 1 second, at every 2 seconds.
The sprite will never say anything.
The sprite will say a random number at every 2 seconds.
The sprite will sometimes say 5, only when x was set to a random variable that happened to be equal to 5.

elements.name: question14
